cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LT, cs.FL

The paper deals with congruence formats for transition system specifications, which is a topic related to logic and semantics. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses stability and divergence requirements, which are related to process algebra and concurrency theory, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also uses inductive decomposition methods, which are commonly used in formal language theory, making cs.LT (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with weak semantics, which is a topic related to formal verification, making cs.FL (Formal Methods) a possible sub-category as well.
